\s+2Other features\s-2

.in .5i
.ti -.5i
\(bu	The interrupt handler will process more than one event per hardware
interrupt.  This change makes high speed RS-232 communications far
more reliable by reducing missed interrupts.

.ti -.5i
\(bu	The clock and date operations in Model III mode will run at the
correct speed regardless of what speed the CPU is running at.


.in 0i
\s+2Incompatibilities\s-2

During development of the "X" and "XD" ROM, only one program was found that
was not compatible with the ROM.    Model III Superscripsit uses a
section of memory that is reserved for the system and is used differently
in the "X"/"XD" ROM.  Superscripsit runs normally, but when you exit to
TRSDOS/LDOS, the DOS prompt is displayed repeatedly, until a key is pressed.
Then the system resumes normal operation.

This glitch can be corrected by applying this patch to Superscripsit:

For TRSDOS 1.3:	PATCH SCRIPSIT/CMD (ADD=6F4E,FIND=3640,CHG=808A)
.br
For LDOS 5.x:		PATCH SCRIPSIT/CMD (X'6F4E'=80 8A)






















